In real-world Azure production environments, region pairs are widely used to ensure business continuity and resilience.

Examples of region pairs include:

* East US paired with West US
* North Europe paired with West Europe
* Central India paired with South India

For example, a global SaaS company might host its primary application in North Europe and replicate data to West Europe. If North Europe faces an outage, traffic is redirected to West Europe.

Another real-life use case is a financial institution operating in India. It may deploy its primary services in Central India and maintain backups in South India to ensure compliance and availability.

A streaming platform like Netflix uses multi-region deployments to serve users efficiently. If one region fails, another region takes over without disrupting the user experience.

These examples highlight how region pairs are actively used in production systems to maintain uptime and reliability.
